freetext.SYMPTOMS_DESCRIPTION: I had 12 hours of low grade fever (100.1) with chills, muscle pain, muscle cramps, and headache. It resolved by the next day.
I had a recurrence of trigeminal neuralgia which I had surgery (micro vascular decompression) on 08/04/20 to correct. It caused severe pain on the left side of my face for 4 days.
